About EBS

















Principals





Research





Consulting Services





Corporate







Ronald L. Eubel

                                Co-Chief Investment Officer
                            


                                Ron has more than 35 years of investment experience analyzing equity, fixed income, and private investments. Prior to founding EBS in 1993 along with Mark Brady and Rob Suttman, Ron was a Vice President, Senior Analyst and Director of Research at an investment firm in Dayton, Ohio where he started in 1982. Ron holds a B.S. degree in Accounting and Finance from Miami University in Oxford, Ohio.
                                
                                Ron is a member of the Investment Policy and Research Committees.
                            


Mark E. Brady

                                Co-Chief Investment Officer
                            


                                Mark has more than 32 years of investment experience analyzing equity, fixed income, and private investments.  Prior to founding EBS in 1993 along with Ron Eubel and Rob Suttman, Mark was a Vice President, Senior Analyst and Director of Portfolio Management at an investment firm in Dayton, Ohio where he started in 1985.  Mark holds a B.S. degree in Finance from Miami University in Oxford, Ohio.
                                
                                Mark is a member of the Investment Policy and Research Committees.
                            


Robert J. Suttman II, CFA

                                President
                            


                                Rob has more than 34 years of investment experience. Prior to founding EBS in 1993 along with Ron Eubel and Mark Brady, Rob was a Vice President and Director of Consulting Services at an investment firm in Dayton, Ohio where he started in 1983. Rob holds a Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) designation and is a member of the CFA Institute. He holds a B.B.A. degree in Finance from the University of Notre Dame in South Bend, Indiana.
	                            
                                Rob is a member of the Investment Policy Committee.
                            


Paul D. Crichton

                                Director of Trading
                            


                                Paul is responsible for trading and operations as well as equity and fixed income research. He is a member of the Investment Policy and Research Committees. Paul has more than 28 years of experience in the investment management industry.  Prior to joining EBS in 1993, Paul was a member of the Research Group at an investment firm in Dayton, Ohio where he started in 1989. He holds a B.S. degree in Finance from Wright State University in Dayton, Ohio.
                            


Kenneth E. Leist

                                Director of Operations
                            


                                Ken is responsible for operations and trading, as well as equity and fixed income research. He is a member of the Investment Policy and Research Committees. Ken has more than 30 years of experience in the investment management industry. Prior to joining EBS in 1993, Ken was a member of the Research Group at an investment firm in Dayton, Ohio where he started in 1987. He holds a B. A. degree in Economics from Wright State University in Dayton, Ohio.
                            


Scott E. Lundy, CFP®

                                Executive Vice President, Chief Compliance Officer
                            


                                Scott is responsible for developing and servicing individual and business clients and serves as the firm's Chief Compliance Officer. He is also responsible for equity research and is a member of the Investment Policy and Research Committees.  Scott  has more than 17 years of experience in the investment industry.  Prior to joining EBS in 2003, Scott was a financial consultant with an investment firm in Florida where he started in 2000.  He holds a B.S. degree in Accounting from Florida Gulf Coast University in Fort Myers, Florida and he obtained a Certified Financial Planner designation in 2004.
                            


Aaron Hillman

                                Senior Securities Analyst
                            


                                Aaron is responsible for equity and fixed income research and is a member of the Investment Policy and Research Committees. Aaron joined EBS part-time in 2002 and full-time in 2004 and has more than 15 years of industry experience.  Prior to joining EBS, Aaron was in the Private Client Services group at Bank of America Securities and worked in business development for a start-up company in Southern California. Aaron graduated Magna Cum Laude from Miami University, Oxford, Ohio with a B.A. in Zoology. He earned his M.B.A. from the University of Chicago's Booth School of Business, graduating with honors.
                            


































